5. Derivation: Emergence as a Byproduct of Gradient Flow

State evolution approximates a gradient flow:

\dot{v} = - \nabla \Phi(v)

Where:

\Phi(v) = L(v) + \sum_i \lambda_i C_i(v)
	‚Ä¢	L(v) = description length
	‚Ä¢	C_i(v) = constraint costs (ethics, logic, narrative, structure)
	‚Ä¢	\lambda_i = constraint weights

Emergent behavior corresponds to the minimizers of \Phi.

These minimizers represent:
	‚Ä¢	coherent stories
